1
00:01:55,666 --> 00:01:57,500
[SETSUKO]
So, what do you say, doctor?

2
00:01:57,583 --> 00:02:00,083
Do you have a prognosis?

3
00:02:00,166 --> 00:02:01,583
Could I possibly look
in Jane's room?

4
00:02:01,666 --> 00:02:04,625
It might answer
some of my questions.

5
00:02:04,708 --> 00:02:08,041
[SETSUKO] Jane has always
been rather antisocial.

6
00:02:08,125 --> 00:02:09,583
But this is important.

7
00:02:09,666 --> 00:02:11,750
Would you be so kind, ma'am?

8
00:02:21,041 --> 00:02:23,833
I put fresh strawberries here.

9
00:02:23,916 --> 00:02:26,000
She loves fruit.

10
00:02:26,083 --> 00:02:29,541
Sounds like a
fruitless endeavor.

11
00:02:29,625 --> 00:02:31,291
Sometimes, the food is gone.

12
00:02:31,375 --> 00:02:33,000
Makes me wonder if
she doesn't secretly

13
00:02:33,083 --> 00:02:34,750
get up in the night
to have a nibble.

14
00:02:34,833 --> 00:02:37,291
[KANZAKI]
That seems a bit of a stretch.

15
00:02:37,375 --> 00:02:42,583
[laughs] But wouldn't it
be fun if it were true?

16
00:02:42,666 --> 00:02:46,416
I absolutely adore
a good mystery!

17
00:03:14,583 --> 00:03:18,208
[gasps] Hello there,
what's your name?

18
00:03:19,291 --> 00:03:21,166
Uh. It's Haruto.

19
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:24,333
Hey. Nice meeting you.

20
00:03:24,416 --> 00:03:27,333
[JANE]
Hm... Haruto, you say?

21
00:03:31,375 --> 00:03:33,708
[JANE] That's a fancy-schmancy
name you've got.

22
00:03:33,791 --> 00:03:37,625
But don't worry,
I know that isn't your fault.

23
00:03:37,708 --> 00:03:39,708
Some people call me Jane Doe.

24
00:03:39,791 --> 00:03:43,125
It's a pleasure to make
your aquaintance, Haruto.

25
00:03:44,041 --> 00:03:48,125
Thank you. You as well.

26
00:03:48,208 --> 00:03:51,291
What do you keep backing
away for, Haruto?

27
00:03:51,375 --> 00:03:55,791
Oh. I, uh, don't know.

28
00:03:55,875 --> 00:03:57,875
Welcome, Haruto!

29
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,166
[HARUTO]
Huh?

30
00:04:00,250 --> 00:04:01,416
Uh!

31
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:02,458
Huh...?

32
00:04:02,541 --> 00:04:05,791
Uh! Uh. Wha--?

33
00:04:05,875 --> 00:04:07,666
Huh?

34
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:12,250
I just adore a good mystery!

35
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:14,375
Come on, Haruto!

36
00:04:14,875 --> 00:04:16,833
[splash]

37
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:25,291
Huh? It's cold!

38
00:04:25,375 --> 00:04:27,916
[JANE]
Hey. What's wrong?

39
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,541
Oh, it's nothing.

40
00:04:29,625 --> 00:04:31,291
Aside from the fact
I can't swim.

41
00:04:31,375 --> 00:04:33,875
[JANE] Oh? And you can't
do anything about that?

42
00:04:33,958 --> 00:04:35,250
This is a dream.

43
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:38,666
Look, water and me are
a losing combination, okay?

44
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:40,750
[JANE]
Hm... Uh...

45
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:42,875
Right! I've got it!

46
00:04:46,250 --> 00:04:47,875
[JANE] You should be
just fine like that.

47
00:04:47,958 --> 00:04:49,291
What is this?

48
00:04:49,375 --> 00:04:50,708
[JANE]
Let's go.

49
00:04:53,375 --> 00:04:55,208
[gasps]

50
00:04:56,041 --> 00:04:59,708
U-Uh... Here goes.

51
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,750
Huh...?

52
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:34,708
[JANE]
Huh?

53
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:38,166
[HARUTO]
This is all a dream.

54
00:05:38,250 --> 00:05:40,291
Pull it together, Haruto!

55
00:05:50,541 --> 00:05:53,041
[KANZAKI]
"Leave everything to me."

56
00:05:53,125 --> 00:05:56,083
But where do I even begin?

57
00:05:56,166 --> 00:05:59,875
I guess I'll start out
by tracking down Haruto.

58
00:05:59,958 --> 00:06:05,208
[warning bells chime]

59
00:06:05,291 --> 00:06:07,125
--[JANE laughs]
--[HARUTO gasping]

60
00:06:07,208 --> 00:06:08,333
Hey! Hold on!

61
00:06:08,416 --> 00:06:11,541
Hold on, hold on,
hold on, hold on!

62
00:06:11,625 --> 00:06:14,083
Whoa. Wait, what are you doing?!

63
00:06:14,166 --> 00:06:15,833
Hey!

64
00:06:15,916 --> 00:06:19,625
[HARUTO gasping]

65
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:24,500
[JANE]
Delightful!

66
00:06:28,791 --> 00:06:30,500
Huh? She's gone?

67
00:06:30,583 --> 00:06:32,458
But where to?

68
00:06:37,791 --> 00:06:43,208
[warning bells chime]

69
00:06:47,375 --> 00:06:50,458
That's incredibly dangerous,
I hope you realize.

70
00:06:50,541 --> 00:06:52,458
Are you all right?

71
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:57,583
[KANZAKI]
She disappeared?

72
00:06:57,666 --> 00:06:59,208
Did you do something?

73
00:06:59,291 --> 00:07:01,333
[HARUTO]
No. I didn't do anything.

74
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:02,791
[KANZAKI]
Hm...

75
00:07:06,125 --> 00:07:08,583
[HARUTO]
Professor K, look out!

76
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:10,458
[BOTH gasping]

77
00:07:10,541 --> 00:07:11,791
[KANZAKI grunts]

78
00:07:11,875 --> 00:07:13,291
[HARUTO groans]

79
00:07:13,375 --> 00:07:14,875
[HARUTO]
Are you okay, Professor?

80
00:07:14,958 --> 00:07:18,500
Uh. Man. This new witch is
starting to be a real pain.

81
00:07:18,583 --> 00:07:22,000
She doesn't seem to
like me very much.

82
00:07:24,666 --> 00:07:27,250
[HARUTO]
She really doesn't like me.

83
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:31,208
[KANZAKI] On the contrary,
I get the feeling that she does!

84
00:07:31,875 --> 00:07:34,541
White is rather drab, after all.

85
00:07:34,625 --> 00:07:36,750
[grunts] Lily!

86
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:38,208
Hi there, Big Brother!

87
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:39,750
Need anything?

88
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:42,458
Surely a girl would be best
to help you better understand

89
00:07:42,541 --> 00:07:45,750
another girl's feelings.
Right, Professor?

90
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:49,458
Oh. I forgot that the
Professor can't see me.

91
00:07:49,541 --> 00:07:51,750
Lily says she wants
to come with us.

92
00:07:51,833 --> 00:07:52,875
Okay?

93
00:07:52,958 --> 00:07:54,708
I'd been hoping to
ask her to join in.

94
00:07:54,791 --> 00:07:57,041
I get the feeling that this
dream is somewhat different from

95
00:07:57,125 --> 00:07:59,041
the ones we've seen before.

96
00:07:59,125 --> 00:08:00,291
[HARUTO]
Hey, watch your step.

97
00:08:00,375 --> 00:08:01,875
You're close to the edge.

98
00:08:01,958 --> 00:08:03,208
[KANZAKI]
Here we go.

99
00:08:03,291 --> 00:08:05,875
[HARUTO]
Uh!

100
00:08:05,958 --> 00:08:08,000
Hey, wait!

101
00:08:10,541 --> 00:08:13,291
[HARUTO] How'd I know it was
gonna turn out like this?

102
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:24,583
Look! Some lights!

103
00:08:30,458 --> 00:08:32,375
I'm going in!

104
00:08:32,458 --> 00:08:34,541
[HARUTO, KANZAKI yelp]

105
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:36,666
[HARUTO screams]

106
00:08:45,875 --> 00:08:50,208
Jeez, Brother! You must've
done something to Jane.

107
00:08:52,250 --> 00:08:53,458
So now what?

108
00:08:53,541 --> 00:08:55,500
Any ideas, Professor?

109
00:08:55,583 --> 00:08:57,458
We know which way
she was heading.

110
00:08:57,541 --> 00:09:00,416
We just follow. It's simple.

111
00:09:01,166 --> 00:09:04,041
[clattering]

112
00:09:04,125 --> 00:09:06,166
What's making that sound?

113
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:08,500
[LILY]
Wow, Brother.

114
00:09:08,583 --> 00:09:11,375
You really must've done
something to upset her.

115
00:09:13,041 --> 00:09:15,541
[KANZAKI, HARUTO scream]

116
00:09:25,208 --> 00:09:28,041
[LILY]
Okay. What just happened?

117
00:09:28,125 --> 00:09:29,166
[HARUTO]
Damned if I know.

118
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:32,166
What's that you're
mumbling about now?

119
00:10:06,666 --> 00:10:09,458
Is this the source
of Jane's Spark?

120
00:10:09,541 --> 00:10:12,041
Wait. What does that mean?

121
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:30,000
♪♪♪

122
00:10:47,166 --> 00:10:49,708
[gasping]

123
00:10:54,291 --> 00:10:55,958
Huh?

124
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:15,458
♪♪♪

125
00:11:18,458 --> 00:11:20,666
[LILY]
Hey, let loose!

126
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:22,500
Come on and dance!

127
00:11:22,583 --> 00:11:26,625
Jane! This is fantastic!

128
00:11:26,708 --> 00:11:30,791
It would be even better
if it wasn't just a dream!

129
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:35,875
[LILY]
Uh. Did she crash?

130
00:11:37,541 --> 00:11:42,500
[electric guitar strums]

131
00:12:00,916 --> 00:12:05,875
[guitar continues]

132
00:12:11,458 --> 00:12:13,833
[LILY]
Uh? What's with the two of them?

133
00:12:13,916 --> 00:12:16,791
Lying around when
there're things to do!

134
00:12:16,875 --> 00:12:20,291
And Professor K left before
we were able to finish.

135
00:12:20,375 --> 00:12:23,166
I wonder if it was
something that I said?

136
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:32,583
[coughing]

137
00:12:33,416 --> 00:12:35,458
[gasps] I know!

138
00:12:38,541 --> 00:12:41,916
[KANZAKI gasps]
So, that's it!

139
00:12:53,583 --> 00:12:55,125
[LILY]
Go!

140
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:01,041
[gasping]

141
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:09,083
[whimpering]

142
00:13:16,708 --> 00:13:18,875
[JANE]
Okay, I won.

143
00:13:18,958 --> 00:13:21,875
Well? Didja get any good shots?

144
00:13:25,166 --> 00:13:29,125
[JANE] Uh... His expression
is a little bit stiff.

145
00:13:29,208 --> 00:13:32,000
Brother's always so
serious about everything!

146
00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:34,791
Hey, try doing it like this!

147
00:13:37,583 --> 00:13:39,166
[JANE]
Put a little motion behind it.

148
00:13:39,250 --> 00:13:41,333
Like you're enjoying yourself.

149
00:13:44,541 --> 00:13:46,958
[JANE]
Meow, meow.

150
00:13:47,041 --> 00:13:49,041
Meow, meow!

151
00:13:49,666 --> 00:13:51,833
Why don't we have him
try this pose?

152
00:13:51,916 --> 00:13:53,833
[LILY] How about we get him
to try this one.

153
00:13:53,916 --> 00:13:56,041
Or this one! It's so cute!

154
00:13:56,125 --> 00:13:58,875
Then it looks like you and I
have very similar tastes!

155
00:13:58,958 --> 00:14:00,916
Let's shoot a bunch
of different options!

156
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,791
[LILY]
Sure thing.

157
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:04,250
[JANE, LILY]
Fight!

158
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:07,875
Come on, Professor.

159
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:13,625
Aside from the technical jargon
I didn't fully understand,

160
00:14:13,708 --> 00:14:16,333
it's nice to know she was
doing something so amazing.

161
00:14:16,416 --> 00:14:19,333
Yes, it's quite wonderful.

162
00:14:19,416 --> 00:14:22,041
It's beautiful to me.

163
00:14:22,125 --> 00:14:23,583
I...

164
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:27,875
I never knew there were so many
different ways of living!

165
00:14:27,958 --> 00:14:31,916
♪♪♪

166
00:14:35,708 --> 00:14:38,833
[LILY]
Brother, you are looking fierce!

167
00:14:42,041 --> 00:14:43,625
[KANZAKI]
How are things on your end?

168
00:14:43,708 --> 00:14:46,708
Do you think you'll be able to
bring Jane back with you?

169
00:14:53,666 --> 00:15:01,375
[HARUTO singing]

170
00:15:10,666 --> 00:15:11,458
[CHILDREN laughing]

171
00:15:11,541 --> 00:15:13,375
Over here!

172
00:15:51,208 --> 00:15:53,458
Huh? You can see me?

173
00:15:53,541 --> 00:15:56,500
[KANZAKI]
Nothing is impossible for us!

174
00:15:56,583 --> 00:15:57,708
[LILY]
Hm...

175
00:15:59,791 --> 00:16:02,958
How can sticking with this
be all right with you?

176
00:16:08,875 --> 00:16:11,875
[KANZAKI]
Ah yes, like peas and carrots.

177
00:16:11,958 --> 00:16:13,416
He made her mad at him.

178
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:15,833
That's because Haruto's
always so serious.

179
00:16:15,916 --> 00:16:17,833
You can't tackle someone
like her head-on.

180
00:16:17,916 --> 00:16:21,041
It takes a pinch of
finesse, y'know?

181
00:16:21,125 --> 00:16:25,041
Uh! Then why don't you head
in there and give him a hand?

182
00:16:25,125 --> 00:16:26,875
Uh...

183
00:16:26,958 --> 00:16:30,583
I'm a fan. I wouldn't
want it to be weird.

184
00:16:30,666 --> 00:16:32,166
What?

185
00:16:33,750 --> 00:16:37,333
[JANE] Haruto, you're the same
as all the others, aren't you?

186
00:16:37,416 --> 00:16:38,875
Huh?

187
00:16:44,125 --> 00:16:45,416
[gasping]

188
00:16:46,291 --> 00:16:47,708
Cheer up, Jane.

189
00:16:47,791 --> 00:16:48,958
It'll be okay.

190
00:16:49,041 --> 00:16:51,916
You don't have to worry.

191
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:55,583
This is the part where I
draw you in close, Haruto.

192
00:16:59,333 --> 00:17:00,500
[JANE]
Jane.

193
00:17:00,583 --> 00:17:02,625
You can't stay in a dream
like this forever.

194
00:17:02,708 --> 00:17:04,875
You have to wake up, Jane.

195
00:17:04,958 --> 00:17:07,833
I know you can do it!

196
00:17:07,916 --> 00:17:09,416
We'll go, together!

197
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:10,458
Come on.

198
00:17:10,541 --> 00:17:13,541
Summon your courage, and rise!

199
00:17:13,625 --> 00:17:17,750
What does a make-believe
world like this have for you?

200
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:20,500
Open your eyes,
and start walking, Jane.

201
00:17:20,583 --> 00:17:22,166
Don't give up, Jane.

202
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:24,291
I know you can do it, Jane!

203
00:17:24,375 --> 00:17:25,708
Jane! Jane!

204
00:17:25,791 --> 00:17:27,625
Jane! Jane! Jane!

205
00:17:27,708 --> 00:17:28,958
Jane! Jane!

206
00:17:29,041 --> 00:17:31,125
Jane! Jane! Jane! Jane!

207
00:17:31,208 --> 00:17:33,708
Ahh! I'm done!

208
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:44,375
It's so annoying.

209
00:17:44,458 --> 00:17:48,416
I wish everyone would
stop humoring me.

210
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:51,916
I'll decide what's best
for myself from now on.

211
00:17:54,375 --> 00:17:55,458
[JANE sneezes]

212
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:56,916
[HARUTO gasping]

213
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,375
What was that?

214
00:17:58,458 --> 00:18:03,416
[sneezes] Sorry,
that's just how I sneeze.

215
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:06,916
Oh, wow! Didja see her
sneeze like a dragon?

216
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,916
I wanna do that.

217
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,416
Well, then.

218
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:12,875
It's about time I walked right
up to the woman and asked

219
00:18:12,958 --> 00:18:14,458
her point blank.

220
00:18:14,541 --> 00:18:15,833
Right!

221
00:18:36,833 --> 00:18:39,791
I'm a fan of cats, too.

222
00:18:39,875 --> 00:18:42,833
Yes. I could tell by looking.

223
00:18:51,625 --> 00:18:54,416
I'd like to smoke,
if that's all right with you?

224
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:57,000
Oh! By all means, smoke away.

225
00:18:57,083 --> 00:19:00,250
I'll also make myself more
comfortable, if you don't mind.

226
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:01,291
There.

227
00:19:01,375 --> 00:19:02,958
My, my. I sure hope
the Professor

228
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:04,375
knows what he's
doing in there.

229
00:19:04,458 --> 00:19:07,291
It's as awkward as an arranged
marriage meet and greet!

230
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:09,125
Did ya hear that?

231
00:19:10,291 --> 00:19:13,208
You shouldn't touch her
stuff without asking!

232
00:19:13,291 --> 00:19:14,208
[HARUTO]
It's no use.

233
00:19:14,291 --> 00:19:15,833
I can't make heads
or tails of it.

234
00:19:15,916 --> 00:19:18,625
[JANE coughs]

235
00:19:22,500 --> 00:19:27,000
Jane, why are you trying so
hard to become a smoker?

236
00:19:34,291 --> 00:19:37,791
As far back as I can remember,
I've always been frail.

237
00:19:37,875 --> 00:19:39,875
And, I grew up envying
the other children

238
00:19:39,958 --> 00:19:42,041
who were able to play outside.

239
00:19:42,125 --> 00:19:43,791
So much that I wanted to do.

240
00:19:43,875 --> 00:19:45,666
But, I shouldn't do this,
or I couldn't do that,

241
00:19:45,750 --> 00:19:47,750
so I did nothing.

242
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:49,625
One day, a snake came
into my hospital room,

243
00:19:49,708 --> 00:19:52,666
and I became friends with it.

244
00:19:52,750 --> 00:19:56,666
But before long, one of
the nurses found him,

245
00:19:56,750 --> 00:20:01,083
and told me that I had no choice
but to "get rid of that thing."

246
00:20:01,166 --> 00:20:03,125
"That thing"?

247
00:20:03,208 --> 00:20:06,875
It had become my friend,
not just "that thing."

248
00:20:10,625 --> 00:20:12,083
I thought since I
was in a dream,

249
00:20:12,166 --> 00:20:14,708
I'd be able to smoke
without a problem.

250
00:20:14,791 --> 00:20:16,083
But I guess not.

251
00:20:16,166 --> 00:20:19,333
Because even here in
my dreams, I cough.

252
00:20:19,416 --> 00:20:20,833
[KANZAKI]
"I'm Home, Jane,"

253
00:20:20,916 --> 00:20:23,833
"Jane's Lollygags", and of
course, "Jane's Spark."

254
00:20:23,916 --> 00:20:27,833
I subscribe to them.
Each and every one.

255
00:20:27,916 --> 00:20:29,708
Those are all your blogs, right?

256
00:20:29,791 --> 00:20:31,583
I love 'em.

257
00:20:31,666 --> 00:20:35,000
It's no wonder that I couldn't
tell who you were at first.

258
00:20:35,083 --> 00:20:37,291
I never would've guessed that
you write your blogs from

259
00:20:37,375 --> 00:20:38,583
inside your dreams!

260
00:20:38,666 --> 00:20:40,125
I like the name Jane Doe.

261
00:20:40,208 --> 00:20:41,916
It's served me well.

262
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:45,625
I don't see how anyone could
dislike the name, but that's me.

263
00:20:45,708 --> 00:20:47,458
[JANE]
It has a nice ring to it.

264
00:20:47,541 --> 00:20:49,458
Average Joe, too.

265
00:20:49,541 --> 00:20:50,958
Names everyone has heard before,

266
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:54,833
but no one knows
who they really are.

267
00:20:54,916 --> 00:20:56,458
It is you.

268
00:20:56,541 --> 00:20:59,250
Not a doubt in my mind.

269
00:20:59,333 --> 00:21:00,583
Changing gears,

270
00:21:00,666 --> 00:21:02,708
would you mind if I asked
you a question?

271
00:21:02,791 --> 00:21:06,333
Sure, no problem. Ask away.

272
00:21:06,416 --> 00:21:08,000
What was it that
Haruto said to you

273
00:21:08,083 --> 00:21:10,541
back there that was
so upsetting?

274
00:21:13,708 --> 00:21:17,000
Haruto told me I wasn't
very good with words.

275
00:21:17,083 --> 00:21:18,250
You're kidding!

276
00:21:18,333 --> 00:21:21,875
He said that to such an
accomplished bloggist?

277
00:21:21,958 --> 00:21:25,708
When someone is right there
in front of me, I'm hopeless.

278
00:21:31,041 --> 00:21:33,541
I am grateful to him.

279
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:36,333
He was willing to
give me a chance.

280
00:21:36,416 --> 00:21:37,666
Yeah?

281
00:21:37,750 --> 00:21:39,375
Does that mean I can see
you again on the outside?

282
00:21:39,458 --> 00:21:42,125
What?! Would you be interested
in being my friend?

283
00:21:42,208 --> 00:21:43,833
Of course.

284
00:21:50,666 --> 00:21:52,250
[JANE] There's something
else I'd like to ask

285
00:21:52,333 --> 00:21:56,166
while I have you here
in front of me.

286
00:21:56,250 --> 00:21:57,333
Tell me.

287
00:21:57,416 --> 00:22:00,958
How long has Haruto been asleep?

288
00:22:01,041 --> 00:22:02,375
[KANZAKI]
Before long,

289
00:22:02,458 --> 00:22:04,333
I'm going to need your help.

290
00:22:04,416 --> 00:22:06,041
[JANE]
Okay.

291
00:23:46,750 --> 00:23:48,625
[LILY]
Sleeping Beauty and thorns.

292
00:23:48,708 --> 00:23:50,625
It almost sounds
like a fairy tale!

293
00:23:50,708 --> 00:23:53,208
But which thorns would put
you to sleep, I wonder?

294
00:23:53,291 --> 00:23:54,916
[EGOS]
Which ones, baa!

295
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:57,958
[LILY] Next time's dream:
"The Thorn Cross Association."

